    <abstract>
      <t>This memo describes the Intel PXE (Preboot Execution Environment) 
remote boot definition (which is part of Intel's Wired for Management 
initiative), and provides the rationale for proposing an extended 
remote boot capability beyond what is currently specified in DHCP.</t>
